<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="247" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,870,1003]" pageId="46" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,870,895]" pageId="46" pageNumber="247">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The only Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[540,659,870,894]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Dasyhelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[540,659,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="247">Dasyhelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which males have yellowish genitalia except for the gonostylus which is dark brown, symmetrical gonocoxal apodemes and paramere located anterior to aedeagus with an arrowhead-shaped posterior portion, and a V-shaped aedeagus with elongate posterolateral arms the apices of which are convergent. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
